1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:04,500
[AI-generated narration] Backup success is not recovery success. ProofRestore verifies recovery before an emergency.

2
00:00:04,500 --> 00:00:07,000
I’ll start with Explore demo vault.

3
00:00:07,000 --> 00:00:12,500
The latest backup job says Completed, but verified recoverability is At risk.

4
00:00:12,500 --> 00:00:18,000
Eight snapshots contain two integrity issues and one retention risk. I’ll click Check a file.

5
00:00:18,000 --> 00:00:23,000
The request asks for my thesis from Tuesday evening.

6
00:00:23,000 --> 00:00:27,000
I’ll select Thesis Final, then open the exact snapshot history.

7
00:00:27,000 --> 00:00:32,000
Recent versions are damaged, while the Tuesday copy is verified.

8
00:00:32,000 --> 00:00:37,500
I’ll keep the time from my request and choose Original location.

9
00:00:37,500 --> 00:00:44,000
The dry run will check for overwrite danger. Now I’ll click Verify recoverability.

10
00:00:44,000 --> 00:00:50,000
The no-key interpreter resolves the path and Tuesday evening.

11
00:00:50,000 --> 00:00:58,000
Deterministic code selects the eligible snapshot, finds the object, and verifies its hash and size. The version is fully recoverable.

12
00:00:58,000 --> 00:01:04,000
Next, I’ll run the restore simulation. This changes nothing.

13
00:01:04,000 --> 00:01:10,000
A newer destination file exists, so ProofRestore flags a conflict instead of overwriting it.

14
00:01:10,000 --> 00:01:16,000
I’ll open the exact evidence.

15
00:01:16,000 --> 00:01:22,000
These entries prove the snapshot, path, object, matching hash and size, and destination conflict.

16
00:01:22,000 --> 00:01:28,000
I’ll continue to the proof report, then generate and download the Markdown report.

17
00:01:28,000 --> 00:01:37,000
It records the request, recovery point, verdict, restore plan, conflict, methodology, and evidence appendix.

18
00:01:37,000 --> 00:01:42,000
Natural language can interpret the request, but only deterministic code decides recoverability.

19
00:01:42,000 --> 00:01:46,500
Backups should not require faith.
